reviews.review_text:
Rumors So Theres this rumor going around that im gonna be leaving the band after the Eugene show, Well thats ab BULLSh$t lie,

GO PHIL
OK Average Good quality recording. Nothing outstanding as far as song choices or concert performance.
memories are much better Although i remember this show as being a great time.The play back is only so so to me, then again anything with Jerry is Good

A slight amendment... On further listening, the last part of set 2 after Space is KILLER, with Garcia ripping out some very Hendrix-like, feedback-drenched licks and the show generally rocking into a heartily satisfying finale. Still, I don't amend my 3-star rating. You're in 12/27/87 country here, boys...
Nice Sounding Show Really good show.  Smooth.  They really mesh well.  Hard to put my finger on just what it is.  Just really diggin this show.  Especially Box through the Jam out of Crazy Fingers.

Cal Expo was hot! These shows were all so good. You had to be there in the rodeo arena to understand how amazing the energy was with three days of camping in a great venue. These shows were phenomenal with a really kind audience vibe. Positive energy!
